title: "qgrav: a software-first R&D platform for atom-interferometric gravimetry"
abstract: >-
  qgrav is a software-first research platform for atom-interferometric gravimetry.
  It simulates a Mach-Zehnder atom interferometer with an emergent gravity phase
  (from a ballistic atom trajectory under a chirped Raman laser), injects realistic
  per-shot noise budgets and a fringe-lock servo over a multi-drop measurement
  cycle, analyses the result (PSD, Allan deviation), and benchmarks against
  published transportable-gravimeter measurements.
